  "text": "transport of endosomes in neurons [CITATION_1] also confirms the relevance of the nanoparticle translocation using the retrograde axonal machinery. Functionalization of Nanoparticles enables them to be endocytosed and transported. It was shown by a study using nerve growth factor conjugated quantum dots that enter DRG neurons and are then transported axonally in a retrograde manner [CITATION_2] ). An additional main pathway to reach the CNS implicates the trigeminal nerve [CITATION_3] , a small portion of which terminates in the olfactory bulbs [CITATION_4] . The trigeminal and olfactory pathways of nanoparticles allow direct translocation to the brain [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . These data suggest an innovative gateway of entrance into the CNS for Nanoparticles, avoiding the blood-brain barrier [CITATION_7] .",
